caption: Cant beat the happy hour here!!
Great food, great place, fast and amazing service. If you like Thai food, it's a great experience!
The best in town. Best curry I've had in Florida

I absolutely love this place! It's classy but not pretentious, and serves the best sushi, sashimi and nigri in town. I've never had a bad experience, the staff is amazing and the chef-level dishes are always changing, adding to the intrigue and giving a sense of a very high-end dining experience. The quality of the foods they offer are unrivalled! My only regret is that I can't afford to eat here every day lol! I highly recommend!

I’m a foodie. Just moved here from NJ/NY and all I can say is wow. Stunning presentation followed by mind blowing flavor. I’m so impressed by this experience. I will be taking all of my friends here to show off such a find. Lychee martinis were perfection and the sushi rolls were spectacular!
Server was Q and he took great care if us and helped with the menu. We got sushi and it came on these huge wooden boards. Cool looking plating. Tasted amazing. Will come again

I did not like this place at all, nothing special for sure. One of my friends thought it was alright, and the other said good. I did not enjoy my food, despite being nicely presented! The outdoor sitting, there was a horrible smell. The bathroom needed attention. I wouldn’t go back there again.
Friendly staff and delicious food. I would say it's a bit overpriced

Absolutely horrendous service. Waitress was unfriendly, never checked on us to see if everyone was ok or cleaned the table after dining. I will never go back again. There are better restaurants in the area with friendlier staff.

I have recently been to this restaurant, I had high hopes given the price tag on the menu items. However, it turned out to be much worse than I expected. I ordered Papaya salad, Pad Thai Lobster, Pad ped Squid, Lychee Nitro tea, and turmeric ginger herbal hot tea. The only decent items were the Papaya salad and the Lychee Nitro tea. Everything else was very low quality and over priced(I ended up paying more than $70). All of this was topped by a terrible customer service. Once the food was ready, there were no napkins or forks and knives, we had to ask for those separately and over multiple times. I do not recommend this restaurant at all, you can get much better quality Thai food elsewhere in town for much cheaper and a better customer service.
Excellent authentic Thai food. We really enjoy the desert, curry and papaya salad...very good service also. True to their flavor and tastes, no fusion food BS.
Amazing Thai food and a perfect location downtown! Went with a group of 10 last night for a birthday party and sat outside. Great service (Up was the best waiter) and amazing food!

This place had horrible service. They broke the number 1 rule with customer service: never argue with the customer. My friend had an allergic reaction to a component of her order. We then asked the server for a new dish and he agreed to give us whatever we would like as long as it did not have the allergy in it. Then when we asked whether the allergy that she had was in the dish, he said no it was not. Once our order was replaced, a new server (supposedly the manager) complained to us that the fish from the order that was returned was very RARE and EXPENSIVE. She then said that the server would usually have to pay for dishes that were brought back to the kitchen. After we explained to her that our intention was not to have the server pay but only to replace the dish, she ran back and told the server a completely different story. The server then storms to our table and says "DID YOU SAY THAT I HAVE TO PAY FOR YOUR MEAL AND THAT I NEVER TOLD YOU WHAT WAS IN THE DISH?" My friend and I were baffled by his expression and tone because he was intending on arguing with us and blaming us for this manager's miscommunication. Overall, the manager told us that their was no component of the allergy in the food when in reality there was. This could have been an extremely dangerous situation and then the staff proceeded to blame us for their mistake. DO NOT GO HERE IF YOU ARE YOUNG AND A POC.
Really nice place with good Thai food

Food was horrible, customer service was horrible. We get sushi all the time and we’ve never had anything that tasted this bad, we didn’t eat anything we got and they tried to MAKE us pay for it, and we still ended up paying 80 dollars and paying for stuff we didn’t even eat half of, never go to this place ever. I’ve never had food this bad in my life, and the worst customer service in the world. We had to argue with them for 30 minutes just for them to take the stuff we didn’t eat off the bill.

A few months ago i ordered tuna from this place and it smelled bad. I told the server and she was rude she told me that tuna wasnt supposed to fresh. Well i understand that but if the fish has gone, bad it gone bad. I got over that and gave this place a secound chance because before covid the food was bomb. However me and my partner went again today to eat and we both agreed food has really lost its quailty for the price. I rather go down the street to dragonfly and spend more money on sushi that taste way better. At this point in the year the pandimic should not be the reason why the food isnt up par.
This place was awesome. Awesome menu excellent food and service. Highly recommended.

Ordered a small delivery toward the end of the night. Arrived super fast. Everything was good. I’m happy to find a miso with no chunks of mushrooms (I’m not a big mushroom fan). Took a photo half way through eating because I was so hungry 😂. Also got a lemonade and they let you choose sweetness level and the “low” is perfect - basically tart and not sweet - just how I wanted it!  (Buddha roll, steamed veg, miso soup)

HORRIBLE SERVICE! I would give it a zero if I could. Do not dine in here just go somewhere else and relieve yourself of having to deal with the TERRIBLE SERVICE of this restaurant. We waited exactly 70 minutes before we got our food and the table next to us who had gotten there about 30 minutes after us got their food before us. It was my first time dining in here having heard such great things before and I was very DISSATISFIED AND DISAPPOINTED with both the food and their service.  We ordered the chicken pad Thai which I normally love everywhere else (it was horrible) and the melting lava sushi (very disgusting). Let me forget to mention they charged us DOUBLE for the pad Thai unbelievable!!!!!!!!  Our waiter was Britney and she put very minimum effort in her job. It is unfortunate because there are so many unemployed people who would be more than happy to have a job and people like this do not value their job at all!
Had the ginger tofu and it was amazing ... and I not eat tofu!  Try the gentleman fig drink.  You will love it.

Mediocre Asian food with nice interior decoration. I came here twice, ordered sushi and thai food both times and was not impress either occasions. The sushi was average, but for the price, I had higher expectations. Thai food was not my favorite, yet my friend seem to like it. Overall, I would not come here again just bc I can find better tasting restaurants at this price point.
Some of the best Thai food in town! The spice is so perfect it lights your mouth on fire in a good way
Love the food here.

Good Ambiance, outdoor sitting option is a plus during corona time. Menu has lots of options for vegan too. Masaman curry is good with jasmine rice. Lots of non alcoholic drinks such as tea and lemonades. Friendly serving staff. Good Thai place overall.

I have Been here 2 times now and everything has been so fresh and delicious. The sushi is fantastic and very fresh and the noodle dishes are perfectly seasoned and portioned. They have delicious and unique cocktails that you can’t get anywhere else along with very quick service. I recommend wholeheartedly!
Good food and friendly service
Food and service was great, it was a little pricey.
thai food at this location - great.
Always super fresh food and such a wonderful variety. It is delicious and worth the multiple visits to try all of their various Thai dishes. This place has been a go to for me for quite sometime now.
Love the food.  I highly recommend the Pad Thai with Shrimp.  Also, they have good Sushi

Only thing I would order again is the spring rolls. I ordered a chicken teriyaki that was super rubbery and overcooked as well as a fried rice that had giant chunks of tomato and more onion than rice. This is a great place to go if you would like to waste your time and money 🚮🗑

The quality of the food is amazing and there are good vegan options. We could taste the freshness of the ingredients, with house made curry pastes, etc. The green curry is the best I’ve ever had! So so good. Also their boba tea bases are all made in house—no powders. This is so rare! I highly recommend.
Great food!!
The staff was extremely transparent about the vegetarian options. They accommodated is with our special requests without making us feel like we were a pain. We really enjoyed the food as well.
Excellent fresh Thai food served with care by an excellent staff! I look forward to trying their sushi.
My favorite Thai restaurant in central Florida! Everything on the menu is wonderful!
Some of the best food I have had in Gainesville
Awesome Thai food, my go to is the Panang Curry with shrimp. Also, best sashimi/sushi I’ve had outside of New York, with lots of options hard to find in North Florida such as sea urchin.

Social fun yes ...however a bit overpriced on quantity that doesn’t present the quality you’d expect suggested by price. Make your own opinions give them a go but don’t get the Thai tea it’s missing something.

Been at If It Is in Gainesville once and loved it.  When I saw that they are shipping, I jumped all over that.  They cooked it and overnighted it with easy prepping instructions.  The food was as delicious as when I ate there.
I have searched for nearly 10 years for Thai fried rice that is as good as the one I had in my hometown. I found it here! That warranted a 5-star review, as I am very picky about my fried rice.
Best drink menu in town and pretty good sushi, stir fry and curry too
I love the vegetable curry and Thai tea! The cucumber and lobster rolls are excellent too!  The blue rice is a nice touch. The staff is friendly and the food always hot or cold as it should be.
Fantastic, authentic Thai. The curries are amazing and fresh.

The food here has been consistently good. My favorite is the pad Thai with chicken and my fiancé always gets the Kaeng Dang curry with tofu. The If It Is platter is a pretty good deal for an appetizer. They have a large tea selection that I'm only just getting into. 😅
Subpar food, drinks, and very overpriced. I would avoid this place as there plenty of other thai places in the area that definitely taste better and not charge an arm and a leg.

I went here once for lunch with some coworkers and I was very impressed. Spacious, wood-accented interior and excellent variety of flavors (the Massaman Curry was a nutty, cardamom-heavy delight). I wasn't able to try the sushi or cocktails, but there were plenty of interesting options on those menus as well. Would go again for lunch or a date night!
Omg does this place really stand out. Sushi was amazing, especially the Toro and Uni. Plus their unique hot teas really add to the meal.
My husband and I eat here as often as possible. We adore If It Is and try something new every time. We will keep coming as long as the doors are open!

I have to tell you all about IfItIs... This place is FANTASTIC. My husband and I went for an early dinner yesterday and they have happy hour specials on food! We had shrimp tempura and the Happy Roll. I loved this roll. It was crunchy and bursting with flavor and a good spiciness. (The jalapeños and cream cheese are best friends.) For dinner I had the house “IfItIs...” curry with chicken. It was so creamy, rich, hearty, a warm spice and their butterfly pea rice is lightly sweet. A magical blend! Our waiter was so nice and he liked that I had questions about the food. I’m a waitress and I usually don’t enjoy too many questions about our food so it was refreshing to be taken care of someone who was so patient. We topped it off with a $4 pot of Chocolate and orange rooibos hot tea. Its so naturally sweet and herbal it was perfect. I am jumping out of my skin to go back.
Loved it! Very fresh sushi, great service, good prices. Will definitely be back.
Amazing happy hour specials, ppl are always friendly and inside is so beautiful.
Food was subpar and overpriced.
Salmon skin roll is superb, the eel roll is a nice starter. Has a great list of whiskeys and sake but kinda pricey. A great place for a social event.

LOVE LOVE LOVE. I can't get enough of their tea and food choices, though, I get the same thing every time I go. I tend to get the Pad See Ew with blooming jasmine tea. That combo is PERFECTION. I also tried their eggplant and sweet potato tempura, and OMG it's a vegetarian's dream. The sauce that comes with is so amazing. I wish I took a picture of my plates because it really was great food. I recommend, when they're busy, and they are often, be forgiving of the staff and the time it takes. They still try to be quick and I have never been disappointed. Worth going.

I have tried a number of "best place for thai food" restaurants in gainesville and was sorely disappointed. I wandered into this place just off of seeing it downtown and was shocked. This is the only place for good, remotely authentic thai food in gainesville. The price point is high but i suspect after considering ingredients, prep time and having a chef with some technique, the mark-up is better than the other places in town. I rarely give reviews but i feel obligated because this is the only place I want to eat thai here and i want them to stay in business. Please eat here.

Got the lobster roll with no avocado and honestly this was one of the best overall sushi experiences I have experienced here in the united states The presentation was striking and whimsical at the same time, the flavors were exquisite and wove a symphony of flavor, the service was prompt and friendly and the drinks (raspberry mint mojito + blackberry margherita oh my god the margherita) were well priced delicious and refreshing Will definitely be back!

This place is absolutely trash, service was horrible and no the place was not packed. Took 30 min to order food. Once the food showed up it was flavorless and bland how it is still open is beyond me. To too everything off when we asked for a box for the "leftovers" the server comes back and states "sorry they're no good we mixed them with other food". So what you're saying is you threw away my food thanks great job. I would rather eat road kill then dine here again. I would have had a better dinner at Mc Donald's at least there I expect to be disappointed.

First off, the service was incredibly slow. It took almost thirty minutes to get our food ordered, the waitress kept checking on the same table, a table that was right next to my own, multiple times but did not once ask if we were ready to order when she would pass by during that time.  The portion size was a bit small for it's price. I have had bigger portions at the same price in many other Thai restaurants. Thank God we ordered multiple appetizers, though with difficulty as the waitress didn't inform us what was sold out on until we asked for each individually. The Pad Thai we ordered was the blandest I have ever had. We ordered hot and it had no spice to it at all.  And the night just ended even worse. The waitress asked if we wanted the left over curry to which I responded Yes. She came back out a minute later and checked if I had said yes that I wanted it. She came back later after I had already paid the check with the tip to say she was sorry but the curry got other food in it. How the heck do you get other food in someone's leftovers if you were supposed to box it up? Sounds more like she forgot and had already tossed it before confirming with me that I had wanted it. She didn't even offer any compensation for the lost food that I had paid for.  This is the worst experience I have ever had. What a great date night to take my boyfriend on, not. How this place has been rated one of the top Thai places in Gainesville is beyond me. 100% would never recommend this place. I wish this could be negative stars!

We went for my husband's birthday dinner tonight and I would say we've visited about at least 10 times since opening. It's one of our favorite places. We enjoy the Thai menu, often have the curries. We also get a California roll for our son and I love that they use real crab. We have always been happy each visit.

Ate dinner here when visiting for the UF family weekend. This is a Thai + Sushi place, close to my kid's dorm. Unfortunately they ran out of Chicken Satay. So for appetizer, we had Spicy Karaage Chicken (which was Spicy) and Charcoal Vegetable Tempura (which was quite unique tasting - we liked it).. Dinner we had Vegetable Fried rice and Pad Thai both of which were excellent. The portion size was about right (at least for us). Definitely will visit again next time we are in town.
Such a cool restaurant! I love their sushi and Earl Grey milk tea. It's kinda pricey but you also get what you pay for quality wise. One of my new faves for Gville.
Food, ambiance, service, and drinks were all on point. We had a great time and will definitely be back!1

Sushi was good. Thai food was poorly seasoned and very sweet. Very unfortunate cause  the venue is beautiful but the service is awful:/ servers liked to argue and honestly had trouble communicating overall.
Really enjoyed the beef pad thai I ordered from them. Flavorful, good portions, and not overpriced. Solid standard Thai food.
Amazing food. The coconut milk base soup is the best ever!

Nice cozy place for quick grabs, vegetarian options are good, 3-7pm is their happy hours for some sushi and appetizers. Decent portions, if you go beyond 7:00 pm the wait time could be more but usually it's about 5 minutes.

Horrible Business ethics is happening at this restaurant. During Happy hour it say “$1.50 for Nigiri” until you read the fine print which says that you have to buy 2 of them equaling to $3. DIRTY TRICK. They didn’t even want to fix it. Imagine buying a shirt for $5 then once you get to the cash register they say “oh you have to pay $10 because if you buy this one you have to buy the second one.” Absolute TRASH! Food was also trash.

Our food was good, but not great. We had the pineapple curry as our main and it was tasty, but not in the top curry dishes I've tried. Their sushi was good and variety in general is superb.  Where this restaurant losses it is on their service. Only go here if you feel like being accosted and/or ignored by your server. When we brought a concern about one of our dishes up to the server, instead of offering a solution, she began arguing with us. Additionally, she never checked-in on us and hardly spoke. We would say "thank you" and she would ignore us. Not coming back.
We enjoyed our time here. Some really good specialty dishes. Sushi was decent. Our table was oddly large for just the two of us.
Great basil friend rice and spring rolls, visit frequently
Great value on lunchtime specials, but warning, they are huge! Food is distinctive and delicious. Service is congenial

This is by far the best sushi place I have had the pleasure of visiting. We came here yesterday afternoon and have now just eaten our third meal! If I were local to Gainesville it would be very difficult to convince me to eat anywhere else. The food was supreme, and the service was warm and all-encompassing. 10/10
Great authentic Thai. The sushi (if u want good quality fish, not talking about fried rolls) you won't get it like this anywhere else in Gainesville. And I've worked at 4 sushi restaurants in gville.
I loved it ! Best sushi ever

Absolutely fantastic, innovative Thai/Japanese fusion restaurant, right in the heart of downtown Gainesville. That authentic style Thai "Doo-Dee" bowl you're looking at and I happily devoured is great.  "If It Is" claims to be the first restaurant in the US to serve Doo Dee. (Stop laughing at the name, folks.) It's a unique variant of a Tom Yum style soup and noodle based dish. You get a choice of 4 or 5 different noodle types, plus protein types. I went with the seafood, which had may scallops, mussels, calamari, and a few more. Chicken, pork, tofu, beef, combos also possible.  Spice options range from "Not Spicy, Mild Spicy, Medium Spicy, Spicy, Thai Spicy." Suggest you order medium spicy if you want a moderate but noticeably spicy bite. Given the authenticity, and my "spicy but not too spicy" preference, I was overly cautious with mild spicy and will go medium spicy next time.  Meanwhile the lunch special my spouse had, in the background, is served on a plank. Wonderful Pad Thai that was very close to the style we had in Thailand rather than at many US Thai places, salad, California roll that was really a step above the usual (yes I snagged a piece), and a Miso soup.  Full sushi menu. Beyond the usual sushi, sashimi, rolls and special rolls, they also have imported or distance-sourced specials that rarely are in Japanese restaurants here. When we were there, they had actual sea eel nigiri with anago imported from Japan, not the common freshwater eel. And Giant Clam geoduck flown in from Washington State. Both were pricey, at $12.95 and $10.95 per piece, but that's reasonable given rarity here and transport. Was tempted but went with the Doo-Dee.  Very good service too.  Definitely try If It Is. We will be dining there again!

Incredible food and drink. We stopped here on our move back to Florida and were thoroughly impressed by every item we had. The Dassai 39 sale was superbly pleasant. Delicate notes of apple and pear were abundant in this clear dry selection. For people not aware of certain sake, there are descriptions of each of the selections on their extensive drink menu. The miso, which is surprisingly overlooked in many restaurants was made to perfection, with just enough miso without making the broth grainy or overpowered. The rice for the sushi was cooked well, with just the right ratio to compliment the fish. Their Otoro was fairly priced and butter on your tongue, the wonderfully marbled tuna shining brightly in true nigiri fashion. The other sushi was superb to say the least. Every soup, noodle dish and side did not disappoint in the least, surpassing my every expectation. I would reccomend this establishment to anyone passing or living in the Gainesville area.
There was a rat running across the beams in the ceiling.
Excellent sushi highly recommend for any sushi lover. This is my second time eating here in the past 2 months
I LOVED my experience here. It's more than just the food. The moment you walk in you enter a unique establishment with a confident aesthetic. I'll be back for sure.

It took 30 mins for us to get our bottle of sake, then 70 mins for us to get our food because they forgot about us. We all ordered the same simple dish basically  In response to owner’s comment: I’d recommend not taking a bunch of reservations that cant be handled by the size of the staff
The food is always good that atmosphere it's great  service it's spot-on
Amazing. Delicious each dish better than the next. Sticky rice to die for

I really appreciated the modern feel of this restaurants and the open doors/windows alongside the seating area was really beautiful. The cocktails are unique, including ingredients like lavender and lychee. Their sushi is good and the blue rice is cool, but the Doo Dee noodles were just okay - a little plain for me. It’s also a little expensive for what you get. Overall, though, the ambience is the main factor in what makes a great experience. I would try again for sure though!
Excellent will return when we go to Gainesville
Very ill interesting take on Sushi
Amazing food and high quality.

Came here for the first time and tried their dee doo soup and it was amazing. It was very flavorful and filling. I also had the pork gyoza which were super tasty and of course I had to get my go to avocado roll which was very fresh. Will be coming back again for sure.

I love spicy food and here they can do it! Thai for real. Their curry is the best. Pad Kra Paow (basil stir fried) is the point. Also They have combination Thai & Japanese like Japanese sea bream lemongrass carpaccio. It’s so gooooooood. Their fish is very fresh. Their rolls are super creation and flavorful. More They have Thai and Japanese fancy cocktails like Tom Yum cocktail (yes it’s not a soup, it’s drink!) Some matcha (Japanese green tea) cocktails. Thai fresh chili and Shiso( Japanese mint) cocktails. Some menu price is a little high, but it’s worth because of the quality. You must try this place!!!!!!!!

Food is very good. If you like spicy, they can make real authentic Thai spice for you. I recommend try their curry (house made paste). If you like fresh fish, they have it! Sofa booth is fit for 3-5 people, so its too big for two people.

A M A Z I N G. This place has ruined me for other "regular" sushi anywhere else. The entire omakase experience is amazing and well worth it. IF IT IS is the perfect place for a special occasion. The consistency and quality are top-notch. You can taste the freshness, and the flavors were amazing and made with such care. The ambience is great for a date night or even hang out with friends.  So if you have never done real omakase before, do a quick Google search on etiquette and if you have any questions at all, do not be afraid to ask chiefs who are friendly, helpful, and professional.  I do not know what to say besides this is the best sushi in town. No, I must say one of the best in Florida!  I have 17pieces nigiri with house made soup for starter and end with dessert.  I would revisit to try their regular menu for sure:))))

I did plan on going here found that they were under a health inspector emergency closure for rat droppings including on food prep surfaces and flies - definitely won’t ever give this place a chance. Gross.

First time here for the entire party of 10 and we ALL loved it! Some ordered the Pad Thai, some got the sushi, and all of us were very pleased. We started at the bar and tried their drink menu, which was kitschy, but tasty. They lost a star for the SUUUUPER delayed wait for our check and that the server never came back to check on drinks or anything! In her defense, she was also working the bar so the poor thing seemed severely overworked. Place I guess is understaffed. Overall, we will all definitely be coming back.
Really great Thai. I loved it.
Expensive...good inari sushi
The food is not as good as the sushi, servers are friendly, atmosphere is quiet we always have a very nice time here.

The name doesn't give away how awesome this place is. My wife and I came in because another place wasn't open yet and we were very pleasantly surprised. Our favorite were the fish all around roll and land and sea roll. We will definitely be back in the future!
The caipirinha made with kiwi was delicious!! Great Brazilian cocktail!

Establishment: The place is dark (which I love). The seats available are parse and leave enough space for people to circulate freely.  Food: I ordered fried rice with pork. It was greasy and I loved it. It is not the healthiest option. If you want something healthy, opt for noodles and maybe something with sea food.  Drinks: cocktails are expensive ($9 for a mojito).  Staff: The waiter that served us was great.  P.S: My comments are based on a student budget (in order words, I am not very rich)
Amazing food and Service.
username: Tonee Francois & THE MAKING OF ICONS

caption: If you are ever in Downtown Gainesville FL this a great gem. There happy hour is one of the best ones in town from 4-7 everyday. Half off drinks and appetizers. Amazing!
Nice place. Good food.

What a disappointment. Food was cold and horrible taste yet, came very late. No knifes on table at all. Manager rudest person ever and she is in restaurant business. We complain about food she came up with lots of lame excuses. Our server was nice but she was the only one trying to serve party of 18. Management sucks big time. This restaurant needs to shut their door permanently.

If I could give this place more than five stars I would. I’ve gone to If It Is as many times as I could get away with since I found out about it in the fall, and every time I’ve gone I’ve been blown away all over again. I went for their omakase for my anniversary and I’ve never had a meal so gorgeous in my entire life. You can come here for something as casual as a Wednesday tuna roll or for as special as a graduation dinner. The curry is spectacular. The sushi is delectable. The chefs go above and beyond in both their preparation and their presentation and you can tell that they put so much pride in their work. The service is so good and so friendly and I haven’t met anyone on the If It Is team that I didn’t love, but I want to give a special shoutout to the wait staff because they really complete the experience. I would recommend this place to anyone who likes sushi, or Thai food, or just food in general. Five stars, ten stars, a hundred stars isn’t enough credit for this place.

I liked a lot about our visit. Most of the food was great. The masaman curry was particularly good. I'd like it to be a little thicker, but the fried scallions were a really nice touch. The panang was the only dish we had any issues with. The kefir lime flavor was overpowering, and the various bits of hard to chew ginger and lime leaves me it less enjoyable. Still I'd come back, just maybe not order exactly the same things.

We waited forever for food and everything came out separately over a 15 min span. Service was slow but server was doing the best she could considering they had her running our large party and several other tables. Server was very nice and apologetic; however, Val the manager was very unhelpful and gave us so many excuses and preceded to argue with us about our experience. Food was yummy but doubt this establishment will last due to poor management.  Management needs to take better care of her employees and customers. Argumentative manager do not lie about us being an hour early because that is an outright lie! Our reservation was for 1pm and we called an hour in advance to ask if 12:00 would work and we were told to come at 12:30. We all got sat and settled at the table just after 12:30 and patiently waited . We don't control how many reservations you take but made ours well in advance and we also dont have control over your menu but you absolutely shoukd get better control of your ability to get the food out in a somewhat timely manner. I was in restaurant management for 11 years and never blammed my patrons for my lack of controlling my establishment.  My graduating daughter is vegan and was excited to try your vegan options  but disappointed mostly with your very rude attitude at this point.

The worse steak I ever order in my life. I live in 7 countries and several States and never have been served such a horrible meal. I definitely won’t come back. The manager try to give me the excuse that tiger meal it’s supposed to be fatty which I agreed but mine was mostly gristle couldn’t even cut it with knife
(Translated by Google) The super attention.  (Original) La atención súper.
Best sushi in Gainesville for a reasonable price.
Excellent and very spicy food. Fast and courteous staff

Enjoyed the food here on a slow Monday night. I ordered the spicy tuna tower with avocado and roe. It was delicious. On a tip from a friend, I asked for them to go light on the sauce, and I was glad I did - otherwise I might not have been able to taste the tuna. (It comes marinated and then served with additional spicy mayo and eel sauce on top, I had them leave the extra sauces off.) Prices are a little on the high side for Gainesville, but the food was good and I'll be back.
Great service by Lucy. She recommended great apptz. Love atmosphere.  Menu has great choices.
Ended up having to wait a long time. The food was good but the wait wasn't worth it ultimately. The sushi came quick and was good though, so order that for sure.
Waited 30 minutes to get a table, even though there were empty tables, and then sat at the table for another 30 minutes waiting for a server to take our order before we walked out
Great cocktails and food!
If

I stopped here for appetizers and drinks during their happy hour in mid March and hated this place. I won't be back because while I was sitting outside at their table and reading their menu I saw bluefin tuna, an extremely unsustainable, controversial, and well-known fish that is close to extinction, all over the menu. The inside is so cavelike and tacky and the outside smells like sewage. The dumplings I ordered were were dried out and cracked, like they had been frozen for a while. The sweet potato roll was beautiful to look at but extremely gluey to eat. The drink hit the spot and the service was good.

We came in for a late lunch around 4pm and had Nina taking care of us as our server. The menu is large and rather intimidating because there are many unfamiliar ingredients and dishes. Nina took the time to literally run us through the menu, explain dishes, and point out her personal favorites. We’ve never had anyone explain all the different dishes so clearly. We decided to go traditional and ordered a DooDee Noodle and a few appetizers. Come by this new place in Gainesville, you won’t regret it. 10/10. Props to Nina. She definitely made all the difference on our visit!
I've loved everything I've tried so far. I will definitely be back.

Hands down the BEST curry and sushi in Gainesville! Pictured is the Red Carpet roll. It was heavenly. The Kaeng Massaman curry is also exceptionally delicious. Great service, lovely presentation, friendly staff! My new favorite spot in town :)

Rather tasty Thai experience. The presentation of the sushi is immaculate; I got a piece of unagi and it tasted delicious. Pretty much any dish you can get from mild to Thai hot. I enjoyed a Panang Curry Hot. The interior is nice and the service is delightful.

The food and atmosphere were good, though there was a ripping black tarp blocking what looked like an unfinished wall that was a little distracting. Our waitress was very sweet! The kitchen seemed a bit understaffed as I noticed some tables waiting quite a while to get food. I also ended up waiting for my order for over 20 minutes after the rest of my group (three others) got their food. The only other thing to comment on was some (what I'm assuming was) truffle dish. A table near ours ordered something that smelled so heavily like kerosene that we all got headaches...maybe cut back on that artificial truffle oil!

We really enjoyed finding this restaurant downtown!  Very good food, drinks and service.  Only problem was a foul odor from the street because were eating outside.  Not the restaurant's fault but did detract from the experience.
Friendly, great food a must try when you're in Gainesville!!!  We had the curry dishes and they were delicious.   Next time we will try the sushi, as it seems to be their thing...
Great lunch specials. Red curry is yummy.
Decent food, poor atmosphere
Great sushi.  Very creative.  Beautiful presentation.  Worth the wait.
Food is great! Always beautifully displayed and great tastes to match. Love that everything is authentic and traditional Thai food. Great place for a date night!

(Translated by Google) 6 people went to the party while the food came out of the party and did not come to me for 30 minutes waiting for the rest of the meal came out the server has no apology ㅡ. The food is small, but the dish is too big to eat. The potati flavor is so thick that I do not have a penalty. I am waiting for the calculations. Picture is lunch special one. Last picture is curry. No spicy, so it's sweet.  (Original) 6명이서 갔는데 일행들 음식 나오고 다먹는동안 제꺼 안나와서 30분기다리구 남들 식사 끝나구 음식나왔는데 서버는 사과두 없어ㅡ.ㅡ 음식은 적은데 접시 너무커서 먹기 불편하구 팟타이 향이 너무 진해서 반도못먹워따 계산 기다리는데두 한세월 걸리구 홀은 넓은데 2명이서 일해서 그런 것 같음 사진은 런치스페셜1번이구 마지막 사진은 커리인데 no spicy 하니까 단맛밖에 없어서 울어따
Great food and variety!
Great food. Great atmosphere. Our server Jake made the experience for my friends and I incredible. Will definitely come back again.

Jake provided wonderful service, was very attentive, and prompt. I've had a number of servers here and he was the most prompt,  and productive server I've had here yet. Previous times its taken 30 minutes to get my drink and Jake got my drink quickly and Continued to check on our table frequently.
Delicious Thai and sushi.  Very good food, a little more extensive, but great quality.  Service is good as well
Authentic Thai food and a relaxing atmosphere

Slow service with good visual presentation but unremarkable taste. Had a bad experience with a group of six for lunch. Ordered a fish all around roll, which did not arrive for about an hour. It was deeply unimpressive and not just because of the incredibly slow service for this roll. Others at the table received their food about fifteen minutes earlier, noodle dishes. Another member of the party had to wait even longer for her roll to arrive. Mark out a couple of hours on your calendar for lunch here.  As far as the food I ordered, mayo on cream cheese dominated the flavors. The texture of the fish on the outside was okay, though I discovered I'm not the biggest fan of baked escolar. This was probably not the roll for me. The garnishes on the plate had no purpose other than to give you something to look at. Spiralized beets, and a dry and unseasoned seaweed hairball. There was also a small section of turnip (?) which looked uncomfortably like a bite of apple placed on my plate. The preparation seemed to have been executed by someone who has seen food on Instagram and decided that visual appeal is the only factor that they needed to take into account. If you just want to take pictures, then you might be satisfied with this.  Two of our party got perfectly serviceable standard fare, pad Thai and fried rice. They were pretty happy with the way their food turned out, but it's hard to mess that stuff up.  One of our party, who enjoys Thai dishes, ordered "Doo Dee" noodles with pork, which apparently tasted strangely and they consumed only part of the dish. The remainder of our party enjoyed their food, including an "uni shooter" that looked fascinating to me.  It's also pretty expensive. I usually don't care, since the usual trade-off is that I get good food in exchange. Unfortunately, this is not a guarantee that they will provide enjoyable or skillfully executed dishes or even attentive service. Consider any of their nearby competitors a better option at similar prices.  If you want some food related visual simulation or a very standard dish, this place is an option. However, given the poor service and culinary disappointment, I'll give this place a wide berth from now on.
Great food great staff!!
The food was great. We went on a Friday night, and we didn't have to wait to be seated. The drinks took a while to come out, but overall a great dining experience.
I love this place!!!
I love the curry and they have really unique sushi rolls with beautiful presentation. The service is just all right but the food makes it worth it.

The menu is very large. Tuna tartare was amazing, the daikon was a new experience for me.  I had the Panang curry and my date had an awesome tuna salad which was impressive to look at. Once this place starts getting a reputation, I'd expect there to be a wait on the weekends. I'll definitely recommend this place and go back. It looks like you can have an extravagant meal or a simple one, depending upon your budget.

Very nice place. The staff was friendly and the prices are super reasonable. There was a small wait when ordering certain mixed drinks, but the restaurant was much busier than anticipated when we arrived, so it wasn't unprecedented.
The waitress was very helpful while we tried to figure out what to order.  The food was good but the prices were high.
Very good food, reasonably priced, great service.
10/10 would recommend to a friend

If it is Kitchen Authentic Thai & Sushi is hands down the best thai food I have ever had. The spring rolls were perfect, the pork dumplings were seared crispy to perfection as well, but the kung pao chicken was outstanding. My buddy had the pa nang curry which was also the best he has had. Our server Jake, was fantastic, prompt courteous and we were in a hurry because we were going to see weakened friends from Portland Maine who played at Le Fest at Loosey's Across the street. If i could give this place 6 stars, I would.

This is my new favorite restaurant in Gainesville. The menu offers a wide range of Japanese dishes, sushi and drinks. Expect to drop $60-$90 for dinner and drinks for 2, but it is well worth it. Staff is extremely friendly (one server came over to chat about my whisky selection because he remembered me from a previous visit. You don’t get that from other establishments.
Food is on the pricier side but all in all great atomospher and great taste.
Delicious and amazing service! Plenty of vegetarian options and I believe some gluten free options as well.

Wonderful Thai menu, that's for sure! As a lover of spicy food, I was thrilled to check it out, and it was very good. The menu is huge, has all the Thai staples (noodles, curry, soups, salads), as well as a robust shashimi and sushi offering. The heat is well versed, from none, to Thai hot. I can recommend the Green Curry, Papaya Salad and Tom Yum soup. There is also a robust drink menu, with "Gator" inspired cocktails, to wine, and a large sake offering (the $5.00 house sake was great for it's price). The restaurant is intimate and classy in design, and the staff could not have been friendlier! Will definitately go again.

Great Thai food!!!! Best I've had since returning from Thailand two years ago. The green curry had the taste that makes it uniquely Thai. I went twice in the weekend I was in Gainesville. I highly recommend this restaurant.
Drinks were great, food was great, service was great. Portions were more than expected, a little expensive but lived up to its price point.
Amazing food. Worth every penny. Goods drinks. Service is ok. Food took quite awhile.
Amazing sushi and food, great varied selection, overall just fantastic in general.

Don't pay the low rating too much thought, the service was mediocre during its opening (which is expected when new restaurants start up with brand new employees).  I've been 5 or 6 times now and the service has been remarkably better each visit.  Every meal I've had there has been spectacular. Their curry, sushi, and Thai dishes are the best I've had in Gainesville (and in the state of Florida) by far. Definitely my favorite place to eat downtown. They also have pretty cool drinks there as well.

My wife and I had a wonderful experience on a Wednesday night. It was not busy when we went. The drinks were unique and tasty (especially the Hot Lips), the Tom Kha was the best I've ever had, and the Bermuda roll was delicious. They even have the good pickled ginger (the yellow kind, not the pink chemical-laced stuff)! The service was great, and our food came out pretty quickly. I've read some of the negative reviews that others have posted, but our experience was nothing like that.

Have eaten here a couple times now. Food is delicious, especially the curries. However, the service is in desperate need of some better management. Our waitress was nice and clearly experienced but the service as a whole seemed very disorganized and not great. To name a few from our last visit, the hostess was wearing an inside out t-shirt and sat us at a dirty table with no place settings, water glasses, menus( eventually a waitress (not ours) came over and took care of these things), our sushi appetizer came out after our entrees even though the waitress said she spoke with them, among other things. Unfortunately for a place that charges what they do this is quite unacceptable. The food could be worth the prices they charge but the price is definitely not proportional to the quality of service, especially with the amount of high quality restaurants with great service in the vicinity of this place. I'll probably go back in a month or two to see if they are able to address these issues (maybe it's just growing pains?) but if they still continue to charge the prices they do while providing sub-par service, I'll probably take this place off my list of where to go out to eat.
Trying new restaurants in Gainesville.
Hamachi carpaccio is a must!
I ate the Thai fried rice last night (9/9/18) and this morning at 4 am I started to throw up and have diarrhea. The chicken was probably not cook right and in return I now have food poisoning.

The low overall rating doesn't do this restaurant justice at all.  I came with a group of four for dinner, and the service was reasonable.  Dishes were brought out one at a time, which is to be expected with authentic Thai cuisine.  When those dishes arrived, every single one was phenomenal.  The food quality is on par with that of some of the highest-rated Thai restaurants in New York, Boston, and Philadelphia.  I'd highly recommend the Doo-Dee Noodle--the flavors and textures in that dish complement perfectly.  The restaurant itself is gorgeous and creates a very nice classy American Thai fusion atmosphere.  I would chalk up any spotty issues with service to the fact that the restaurant is nearly brand new.  This place deserves a full crowd!

Food was very good, they offer a variety of Thai and sushi choices. Sushi was a little expensive but very good. Great unique atmosphere, my only complaint was the service a bit slow especially for a Thursday. I am however excited there is another Thai food option in town!
Food was really great, but also hard to enjoy after waiting 1.5 hours for it.

A little on the expensive side but the lunch deals there are well worth it. Easily the best Thai food in Gainesville. I saw a few reviews complaining about service, but I really haven't had a problem with it. In fact, I've had above average service each time I've been so far.

Waited 20 minutes without a single person acknowledging our presence at the table. Complained to hostess, who did not seem to care. Half of the restaraunt was empty. Poor customer service. I have no idea what the food was like, because I left and had a fantastic meal at Emiliano’s.

I had originally given this place five stars. However, I no longer believe that they deserve it. We came to the restaurant and were asked if we had reservations. We did not have reservations but the restaurant was largely empty. We waited for 20 minutes and were then seated. Once at our table, we waited an additional 20 minutes. Not a single person came to the table. I alerted a waitress that we had not been seen, even for waters, and she simply replied “oh, okay”. I went back to my table and waited an additional five minutes, we still had no one come to see us. We finally got up to leave and I asked to speak to a manager (mostly because I had really enjoyed this place the first time I had dined here and wanted to alert them of this issue). The waitress seemed unwilling to let me speak to anyone. They were not consolitary in any way and were quite dismissive of the whole situation. I am extremely disappointed because I had really raved about this place to my family before I brought them here. I will not go back. If you enjoy even mediocre service (actually, any service at all) I wouldn’t go to this establishment.

Fiod was delicious, service not so much. The woman was trying hard and i understand they just opened but 30 mins for drinks is just too much. No soy sauce bowls on the table for the soy sauce and  rice was late with the meals. I will come back cause i know they just opened but if i experience what i did again I will not be bringing my business back.
Worst Thai I've ever had. Pad Thai was bland and dry.  Pad See Ew was incredibly dry and full of bitter leaves.  Won't be coming back.

Had dinner with friends and I was pleasantly surprised how good the food was. Had a sushi roll and tempura for appetizers which were decent, something I find rare at places that don't specialize in Japanese cuisine and sushi. I ordered chicken prepared in the house "If It Is" curry at one level below the "Thai hot" maximum heat. It wasn't blazingly hot but was very flavorful and delicious, the chicken very tender and good. Service was friendly and attentive. Very pleasantly surprised, this place may be my new Thai go-to in town instead of Bangkok Square. Will definitely visit again!
Humid and smoky inside the restaurant. Waited 50 minutes for a table only to be forgotten about by waiting staff. Even more poor service than what you would expect for a new restaurant.

Worst customer service. Manager Up didn’t even bother to come to talk to us. We found fly in our beer and we were scared it might be in our curry as well. Someone from the kitchen came in and was in complete denial about the fly. They took over the dish to the kitchen to investigate to see if there is any fly in the food. Who does that???  We ordered 2nd curry and it tasted the same no difference. Average quality food and overpriced.  I just want to let everyone know that if you find something in your food please take the pic.
Amazing food

Wow If It Is incredible!?? I went and sat at the bar and ordered a variety of nigiri, each time pieces came out it was like art, the seafood was so fresh, and the staff were friendly, the sushi chef even taking time out to explain things and ask how i might like my sushi prepped. I highly recommend. I got pad thai to-go which was also very good. Best sushi and thai in gainesville

What a disappointing dinner and a joke of a restaurant.  Had dinner with the wife. Menu is 8 pages large with two separate menus for happy hour (that ends at 5?) and cocktails. Troubling sign to have so much on the menu.  We order: 1. Hot appetizer 2. Sashimi 3. Sushi roll 4. Masaman curry And drinks to boot.  I say “first we will begin with a hot appetizer” and continue with the order.  3 minutes later, the curry comes with room temp rice.  There is no silverware. There are no plates. No one comes for 5 minutes to ask about food or bring these items. I got up and collected my own utensils and plateware.  The curry is souplike in consistency with no thickness, no heat whatsoever despite being ordered “very spicy” and is bland. I ask the waiter why the curry came out first. Response?  “You put it all on one ticket so its whatever is ready first gets served first.”  Say what?  Sashimi tasted like unfrozen tilapia.  Sushi deep fat fried and still didnt taste good.  Hot app came out last, whitefish and was bland an unpalatable.  Drinks have no alcoholic component to them, my cocktail with hibiki japnese whiskey is drowned in juice to the point of being indistinguishable from the sugary fruit drink.  This cost over $80. What a f*&king joke. The hard and fast rule still holds true, if a place tries to do too much they do nothing well. I obviously wont be going back into this disappointing money pit, and hope you avoid the same fate by reading this word of warning.
Amazing service & good food! Might want to consider removing live plants due to nats.. but other than that.. good addition to the downtown area!
Greatest Thai food in town without a doubt. Loved the Sushi!

We were there celebrating a special occasion but the experience did not match our expectation. I ordered lobster pad Thai and the waitress came back after 5 minutes and said they were out so I asked for MILD beef pad Thai. We got 3 out of 4 food that our table ordered. We started eating and my food was super spicy. I tried the food my husband had and that was not as spicy. We asked the waitress to change the food. She expalained that they are sometime inconsistent with spice level. Shortly after, the dish was redone. The 4th fish our table ordered is still not here. My food had a burning smell and tasted bitter. At this point, I do not want them to redo my food but what really bothers me is that the waiter tells me the burning taste is because it is “Authentic”. In addition to all of this, we paid for  a dish that I didn’t eat. Very disappointing! I will not go back

Just dined there and wow is the service terrible, we spent an hour and a half and only 4 of us got our main entrees out of 9. The food was good but not worth the price or the wait that came along with it. The sushi was really good and thankfully I ordered that with my water and it still took 30 minutes to come out! Also our server argued with us that our food had taken only an hour to come out... 4 out 9... for thai... enough said

Arrived at 7:45, seated at 8:30. Gyoza's took 30 mins to come out and were room temp. Entree's didn't come out until 9:30 and weren't hot either. They just opened but still... If you're going to make me wait that long for my food, at least bring it while it's hot.

Best new restaurant in Gainesville. The fish is imported and never farm raised. Attention to detail and a nice atmosphere make this place a new experience in town. I believe this place will set a new standard for restaurants in Gainesville.

This place has marketed itself as a high end chic modern restaurant but in reality, it’s highly overpriced and the food is bad. I had the same noodle they had in a photo on their menu and it looked large enough and delicious but when I got it on my plate, it was terribly salty, not to mention the much smaller portion. My friend had a curry and it came out with rice that was somehow dyed in BLUE. We all lost our appetite after seeing the rice. For this, I ended up paying $18 with tips. Not worth the trip and money.

Pros: The food hands down is the closest to what I had in Thailand. Our entire party had several curries my favorite was the Panang curry. I love their attention to details like monogrammed silverware and the contrast dinnerware setting. It shows that the owners have put in a lot of work into this restaurant. Cons:Their appetizer platter was a sad affair though, the sauces were delicious but the dumplings were cold soggy and oily. The chicken potstickers were dry and cold, and the tofu was cardboard. Their staff needs more practice too, just small things like refilling the water pitcher or getting plates and silverware  when the food comes is something that needs more attention. Our server was very friendly.

I just had a delicious vegetable pad thai, a little bit too sweet in my opinion. I guess the chef wants to please the american palate. The calamari was okay, I find it very expensive for only five pieces... I want to come back and try other dishes. Good service and nice atmosphere.
Ordered food to go. Showed up 25 mins later and they forgot to put it in. I cancelled and went to dragon fly. They don’t have it together here yet.
I had sushi during the soft opening. It was amazing. Tried the curry on opening night. Equally as amazing. Service was impeccable on both visits. I highly recommend downtown’s newest addition.
Delicious food and cocktails! Everything we ordered tasted amazing and was beautifully presented. The staff was very nice too. This place is a new favorite.
Delicious pad Thai and the $1 Dollar Old Fashioned was amazing!
Authentic Thai menu so don’t be afraid to ask questions! Super friendly & knowledgeable staff. Delicious fresh ingredients. We’ll definitely be returning!

I'm delighted that we have a high quality Thai restaurant on our side of town.  Since the soft opening I've visited three times.  The waitstaff has proven to be knowledable, the food delicious and beautifully presented as well as top-notch sushi.  The sushi chef, Dale, was a helpful guide to us throughout one of our visits.  I highly recommend this restaurant for its quality, its unique compliment to downtown and for the authentic Thai cuisine that will not disappoint.

Amazing service. Amazing food. Decor is great. I have been there 4 times since opening. I am impressed by the quality of food, attentiveness of their wait staff and overall satisfied. Even during their soft opening, I understand that not everything is perfect, but they went above and beyond to make sure I was content. They deserve 500 Stars!

SO excited to have a solid Thai choice on our side of town. The beef carpaccio sushi app was incredible. The Pad Thai was one of the best I’ve ever had (a staple dish to see how good a Thai restaurant really is IMO). The green curry was good, but could use some tweaking. Admittedly, this may just be my Americanized palate, but I like it a bit more sweet and less salty. 3 star spice level was perfect - just spicy enough to make me sweat but not be uncomfortable. Loved the blue rice touch. My wife got the 1 dollar old fashioned - awesome flair and presentation. The service was spotty, but I chalk this up to a soft opening. Looking forward to seeing what this sushi chef brings to the ‘ville. We’ll undoubtedly be coming back.
Great food, great service, and the restaurant looks great.  Hope this place flourishes ..

I cannot believe that this kind of quality asian restaurant is in Gainesville. I have not had a good pad thai for years and this place’s pad thai just blew my mind. My girlfriend had Panang curry and it was super impressive. I also had a today’s special nigiri, Kinmedai, and it was jaw dropping experience. This place is the most authentic and best asain restaurant I ever been to since I came to the US. Want to give 6 stars if possible.

My coworker and I went today for lunch. We got there around 11:45, and there were only a few other people in the restaurant. My coworker asked the host who sat us about the nigiri; the host replied he had been working there only a day, and to wait for our server (ok, no big deal). We both ordered an appetizer, and that's when things started going downhill. My appetizer came out on a comically large wooden pizza peel which took up the entire table; his, shortly thereafter, on a normal-sized plate (he ordered to pieces of nigiri). From that point, we did not see our server again until the end of meal. We ran out of water pretty early, and we could not get in touch with the server. Still, we waited. After about 20 min, my main course came out (beef pad thai). The odor coming from the plate made both my coworker and me absolutely nauseous--neither one could eat more than a bite--and I ended up leaving the entire plate there. After an additional 30 min, a total of about an hour now, the server finally came back. She asked my coworker, who had still not received his sushi, if he were still waiting on his sushi. Yes, he was. She explained that "[they] sent the other sushi chef home this morning, so there's only one guy in the back making sushi" and that it would be an additional 5-10 min. At this point, our lunch hour was over, and my coworker indicated that. She offered to bring out a box for him so that when it arrived, he could box (not box it to go behind the kitchen or anything). She went away and came back with a box shortly. After another 10 minutes, she came out with her tablet and explained the order had never gotten to the kitchen. At that point, we asked for our checks. She came out and handed us the checks, nonchalantly stating "next time you come back, we'll have a full staff." Aside from the Stygian service, the bill totaled over $30 for my friend and $20 for me. For a $50 lunch we received one edible appetizer.  TL;DR: If you like fasting, hate service, love foul smelling food, and hate money, give it a try.
Everything my friend and I ordered was amazing and the presentation was like something out of a magazine. The drinks were delicious as well, I can't wait to go back.

The atmosphere is so peaceful and beautiful. The sushi bar is my fav. The chefs are knowledgeable and really cool to talk to. All the wait staff are attentive and good energy. I'm also stoked about their tea bar selections. All authentic thai ingredients with vegan/ organic options. I love the diversity Gainesville keeps offering.
Amazing place: excellent food; great teas; friendly service.

Attended the soft opening. Food quality and variedv are top notch. Would recommend their cocktails at they are quite unique and tasty. The curries and sushi are also quite nice. Glad to see new high quality Asian options in the city.  Service was on the slower side, but this could be attributed to the wait stuff working out the kinks before the opening. Definitely worth a trip.

This place is VERY good. My girlfriend is Thai and she's been here 11 years, she said this was easily one of the most authentic places she's ever been.  We had the Thai coffee and lunch special Curry and Pad Thai.  Don't go in expecting chopsticks - Thai people mainly eat with spoons and they don't use chopsticks much at all and Don't order Thai spicy unless you're crazy! You can always ask for the spice tray to add spice if you want to.  We were only there for the soft opening but will be back asap. The place was perfect. I would not recommend sitting outside - it smells really bad and there's nothing that they can do about that.

Ambience and customer service is top tier. The cocktails and foods are well presented, creative, and absolutely delicious. Price point is very reasonable and the portions are generous. Overall overjoyed to have a new go-to spot in downtown.

I was pleasantly surprised and appreciate the effort they’ve put into the experience through: decor, flatware and flair from the omosake bar. But let’s get down to the food: there’s a 5-point rating scale for heat and an extensive list of Thai goodies and teas to choose from. I overheard my neighbor say “he hasn’t had flavors this quality in the States” and I may have to agree. Had the lunch menu Pad Thai, which was large enough to share for two and the perfect bite of sour, sweet, salty, and spicy. I look forward to trying the wiggly crustaceans next time!

Very impressed. Really good Thai flavors with very helpful staff, based on a recent soft opening lunch experience (Thai Fried Rice, Pad Thai, Soft Shell Crab). Surprised to learn this is the first location opening in the United States. I was unfamiliar with the brand but after some quick research, the fusion-confusion aspects from decor, menu design, and food selections have to deliberate. This unpredictable dining experience (I had so many questions) adds to the charm actually, and reminded me of meals overseas.

I can't be too harsh because they're only in the soft opening stage, and I'm optimistic about the future direction. The staff was very friendly and attentive. I'm a little confused by the decor but that's a minor detail. My companions ordered the Pad Thai lunch special and the Red Curry lunch special. They said the noodles weren't quite right and both were comparable to Taste dishes. I ordered pork gyoza, and the filling itself was tasty but the wrapper was pretty dried out. My companions and I also agree there are a few cosmetic changes that could go into the menu. Overall I'm looking forward to coming back during or after the grand opening for a larger meal and a cup of tea!
